Most of my time is spent mainly in Mazatlan, where I own a condo,  to play tennis and then about  5 days in Puerto Vallarta to Salsa dance. It is the dolce Vita ( sweet life) ,sunny and day time temps of about +28.

I  enjoy hosting on Airbnb mainly because I like meeting new people and having people come from around the world. I use Airbnb whenever I can for traveling around the world because it is so affordable.   Dom and his wife Jessica live close by my home and are co hosts with my airbnb. 

Silvio

Like it’s neighbour to the north, South Osborne is a groovy section of the city where cool kids congregate while, due to the abundance of families in its Riverview and Lord Roberts neighbourhoods, it also has a very cozy, friendly neighbourhood sort of feel.

The south part of Osborne Street cuts a line between these two neighbourhoods, which are some of the oldest residential areas of Winnipeg. Sandwiched between these abodes is a street chock full of fantastic casual eateries, along with The Park Theatre, arguably Winnipeg’s busiest venues for live music film and artsy happenings. New fully equiped Sports Complex/Gym within walking distance (Sport for Life Centre).

Located on Waterfront Drive, our second level condo boasts picturesque views of downtown Winnipeg and the famous Canadian Museum for Human Rights. Waterfront Drive is a modern day thoroughfare that’s on its way to becoming one of Winnipeg’s most prestigious places to live, work and play. Stephen Juba Park, is located just minutes from our condo by foot. A beautiful waterfront park that runs from the Exchange District to Downtown Winnipeg. The park features walking trails, bike paths, landscaping and a Water Taxi dock. The parks open areas feature public art works by local artists.

In the summer, enjoy legendary desserts like the "goog special" (a blueberry milkshake topped with banana ice cream and hot fudge) which have made the Bridge Drive-In one of Winnipeg’s most renowned locales for more than 50 years. This walk-up summertime ice cream spot is just a short stroll from the pedestrian Elm Park Bridge and sees vast line-ups throughout the season.

In recent years, a handful of new shops and eateries have also opened in the area. At Chaeban Ice Cream, enjoy small batch, naturally made ice cream in incredible flavours like Abir Al Sham, a traditional Syrian recipe with rose water, orange blossom, toasted pistachios, ricotta cheese, and orchid root powder. name: Loft in Winnipeg · ★4.96 · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Staying in the slower-paced East Exchange means an easy 15 minute walk along the tree-lined Red River to Old Saint-Boniface, the Forks, Shaw Stadium, and the Canadian Museum for Human Rights.

Saint-Boniface Hospital is a 20-25 minute walk over the Esplanade Riel and down Avenue Taché. Health Sciences Centre is a 20-25 minute walk down McDermot Avenue.

Equally close are MTS Centre, the Burton Cummings Theatre and the Metropolitan Theatre.

Winnipeg's modern business district, Portage & Main, is a 5 minute walk up Rorie Street.

Within the immediate vicinity of Le Loft 139 are the Royal MTS Theatre, the Warehouse Theatre, the Centennial Concert Hall, the Manitoba Museum and a plethora of restaurants, pubs, coffee shops, art galleries and boutiques.
host_about:
On est un couple du même sexe originaire de Winnipeg, au Canada. Ensemble depuis vingt-cinq ans, on a habité en Suisse, en Espagne et au Canada.  On aime beaucoup cuisiner, mais en voyage on préfère dénicher des restaurants préparant des spécialités locales. Terre-à-terre, proches de nos familles, on apprécie tout particulièrement prendre un verre en compagnie de bons amis.


Quelques destinations ou voyages mémorables: le parc national Kruger et une bonne partie du reste de l'Afrique du Sud en self-drive; un voyage en cargo du Pirée (Grèce) jusqu'à Tanjung Pelepas (Malaisie) en passant par le canal de Suez, Jeddah (Arabie saoudite) et Colombo (Sri Lanka); Naples - une de nos villes préférées;  et la Jordanie en self-drive avec, comme cerise sur le sundae, une visite de la ville ancienne de Petra.  


We're a same-sex couple originally from Winnipeg, Canada. We've been together for over nearly 25 years and have lived in Switzerland, Spain and Canada. While we enjoy cooking when we are at home, we love going out to restaurants when we are on the road, trying new dishes and seeing how other people live and see the world. Down-to-earth and close to our families, we appreciate simple evenings sharing a good glass of wine with friends both new and old.

A few memorable trips: a self-drive safari in Kruger National Park (South Africa), sleeping under a star-filled sky in the Wadi Rum, Jordon, and a trip on the Hatsu Courage (a container ship) from Piraeus (Greece) to Tanjung Pelepas (Malaysia).  And, of course, Naples - one of our all-time favourite destinations.   While in Switzerland, we had the opportunity to travel to many European, North African and Middle Eastern destinations. 

Wir sprechen auch Deutsch. 
Parliamo anch'italiano.
Hablamos también español.

host_about:
Hello, we are Jason & Taylor!

As working professionals (Pilot/Teacher) and avid world travellers we love meeting new people, experiencing different cultures and exploring new places.  

We have travelled to over 30 countries; enjoying the cold of the Arctic, scuba-diving beautiful Ocean reefs, the jungles of Asia, and the mountains of Central America.

We are well-versed in Winnipeg and surrounding areas.  We frequent local sport, art, and cultural events. As foodies we have a great list of our favourite local restaurants, pubs, and coffee shops! 

We love meeting people from different parts of the world and we look forward to connecting with you.  We will do our best to make your stay as comfortable as possible, providing any information and assistance you need (or being a good guest, depending on our role).

name: Loft in Winnipeg · ★4.89 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Winnipeg's Exchange District is one of the most exciting and trendy neighbourhoods in Winnipeg. There is always something to experience. Stroll along the beautiful landscaped walkway on Waterfront Drive, explore some of the finest preserved historic architecture, or simply relax in Stephen Juba Park which is just steps away from the loft.
The Exchange District thrives today as one of Winnipeg's commercial and cultural centres, as well as an assortment of restaurants, nightclubs, and art galleries.
within walking distance you will find the Manitoba Theatre Centre (right across the street!) Planetarium, Science Gallery, Pantages Playhouse Theatre, Centennial Concert Hall, which houses the Royal Winnipeg Ballet, Symphony Orchestra, and the Manitoba Opera. The Goldeye's Baseball Stadium, Historical Forks, Children's Museum, and the Museum for Human Rights are only a short 10-15 minute walk. The MTS Centre which houses hockey games, concerts and other events is a 5 minute walk. On

name: Home in Winnipeg · ★4.66 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview:
You’ve landed in Charleswood, the semi-rural community of forest trails and family-friendly eateries. Joggers, cyclists, and bird-watchers are abundant, as they embrace the combination of great places to eat with verdant greenery.

Here, you can hop on the Harte Trail, which runs for 6.5 km through an old railway bed and is part of the Trans Canada Trail, or stroll through Assiniboine Forest with 700 acres of wilderness and trails for exploring. After you’ve worked up an appetite, pop into Capital Grill and Bar where chef Wayne Martin offers an updated take on comfort food using Manitoba ingredients.

Bordering Charleswood is the can’t-miss attraction of Assiniboine Park. You can really spend your whole day here, as you watch polar bears swim overhead in the viewing tunnels of Journey to Churchill at the zoo, take the kids to the Assiniboine Park Nature Playground, enjoy a calm walk through the English Gardens while checking out the beautiful bronze sculptures at t

name: Bungalow in Winnipeg · ★4.67 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 shared bath
neighborhood_overview:
St. John's is one of the more established neighbourhoods of the North End, its development occurring shortly after the turn-of-the-century and being virtually complete by the mid-1920s. Residential structures pre-dating 1900 can be found on most streets in the neighbourhood. Churches, retail structures along Main Street, schools and other amenities have also been established through the years.
St. John's was part of the City of St. James when it became part of the City of Winnipeg which came into legal existence on January 1, 1972.
(taken from: the City of Winnipeg website)

Check out our extensive guidebook (see other listing: "Cozy Bungalow - Great Locations!") for info on nearby (and not-so-nearby) places to check out during your stay!

name: Condo in Winnipeg · ★4.93 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Off the lobby we have Hildegard's Bakery. Directly adjacent to the building and within a 5 minute walk you will find dozens of great restaurants ranging from pubs, to sushi, to Thai food - Whatever peaks your taste-buds' interest on that given night.

From the lobby, you can see a Rexall Pharmacy, convenience store, McDonald's, and Tim Horton's, all within a 30 second walk.

Only a 5 minute bus/cab/car ride away is the Canada Life Center (Go Jets!) and 5 minutes further from there is the Exchange District with all of Winnipeg's most popular restaurants, pubs and nightclubs. Within 10 minutes you will also find the Manitoba Legislative Building, Human Rights Museum and The Forks, a Winnipeg must see.

neighborhood_overview:
St. Boniface is home to one of the largest francophone communities west of the Great Lakes, and it is the heart of Manitoba's French history and culture. While here, you can stroll along le boulevard Provencher and visit boutiques and quaint cafés along the way.

Gaining buzz in the French Quarter is Marion Street Eatery, which serves stylized comfort food for breakfast and lunch. Other notable eateries include: Resto Gare, where authentic French cuisine is served aboard a refurbished train car; Promenade Café and Wine with gorgeous views of The Forks and the downtown skyline; and Le Garage Café, which is constantly packed with live music lovers and is renown as one of the best poutines in the city.

name: Loft in Winnipeg · ★5.0 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Winnipeg's Exchange District stands as one of the most iconic and vibrant neighborhoods in the city. Designated as a national historic site, this area boasts an exceptional collection of heritage buildings constructed between 1880 and 1920. Fondly referred to as the “Chicago of the North,” the Exchange District showcases over 150 immaculate heritage buildings across a 20-square-block area. Once serving as warehouses and “terra cotta skyscrapers” housing financial institutions, these structures have now been transformed into Winnipeg’s cultural hub, flourishing with a diverse array of restaurants, galleries, gourmet donut and coffee shops, as well as hip clothing, lifestyle, and design stores.

Our loft, located in the heart of the Exchange District, offers an outstanding experience steps away from the river, with a beautiful walking and biking trail. It's a walker's paradise, where you can enjoy a pleasant stroll along the river for 10 minutes to reach Goldeye's Shaw Baseball
host_about:
" We travel the world over in search of what we need and return home to find it" 

As a little girl, I always admired the way a space and its’ contents have the ability to create memories and feelings. One of my earliest realizations of that experience was when my family and I spend a Christmas at a refugee camp when I was 10 years old. We had just escaped communism, leaving everything behind, yet my parents managed to create for us a lovely corner in our room with a small decorated Christmas tree, a bowl of nuts, some Mandarins, and even a few small presents. I still remember wondering how they managed to put this together for my sister and me? It was the loveliest feeling and that wonderful memory is still vivid in my mind as one of my very favorite Christmases. 

Perhaps it is this experience in leaving our life and all our worldly possessions behind to start again, which makes me always pause in a space and take in how it makes me feel. I truly believe in the wonder and emotional connection to the things that we choose to surround ourselves with. 

I have also been fortunate to put my head down on a pillow in many lovely places during my 20 years of executive global travel. I have come to appreciate that there are a few essentials that have always put a smile on my face and made me feel at home while traveling away from home. It is with this mindset that my family and I have approached the creation of this loft, our special space. 

A beautifully-appointed loft, with comfy bedding and linens, lovely amenities, all the comforts of home, and an opportunity to connect with locals, are but a few of the things that we hope our home and family can offer. We are passionate about our city and would love to share everything that may be of interest to you about Winnipeg. There is so much to discover and talk about in English, French, or Czech if you prefer.
We look forward to meeting you.

neighborhood_overview:
The St. James area in Winnipeg, Manitoba is a vibrant and thriving neighborhood located in the western part of the city. Known for its sense of community, diverse amenities, and convenient location, St. James offers a wonderful blend of residential charm and urban convenience.

One of the highlights of the neighborhood is the iconic Polo Park Shopping Centre, one of the largest retail destinations in Manitoba. This premier shopping destination boasts a wide range of stores, boutiques, restaurants, and entertainment options, ensuring that residents and visitors have everything they need right at their fingertips.

St. James is also home to a variety of parks and green spaces, providing ample opportunities for outdoor recreation and leisure. Assiniboine Park, located nearby, is a major attraction, offering beautiful walking trails, picnic areas, the Assiniboine Park Zoo, and the Leo Mol Sculpture Garden. If you’re strolling into the area from downtown, enjoy the public art that has been integrated into the Osborne Bridge design to emphasize the eclectic nature of the neighborhood. The bridge is a major river crossing and one of Manitoba's busiest routes for vehicle, cyclists, and pedestrian traffic.

name: Condo in Winnipeg · ★4.46 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Wander around downtown for the day and you'll find yourself surrounded by Winnipeg’s famed architecture, a mix of turn of the 19th century and early 20th century masonry (or, as we like to say, stone skyscrapers) and modern glass buildings. You’ll also be introduced to downtown’s culinary scene, where gourmet sandwiches, food trucks, and handcrafted cocktails are aplenty.

Above all, you’ll see the people that make this place so great - like the singer/songwriters on stage at downtown’s many live music venues, the tour guides who can introduce you to landmarks like the much-photographed oculus at the VIA Rail Station, the chefs and shop keepers of the trendy boutiques and restaurants, and our famed Golden Boy, who looks out from his perch on top of the Manitoba Legislative Building.

neighborhood_overview:
Overview

The home is nestled in a tranquil and friendly neighborhood of Winnipeg, Manitoba. Its prime and well-connected location offer a relaxing retreat less than five minutes from the booming downtown.

One of the top attractions in Winnipeg is The Forks, a historic meeting place where the Red and Assiniboine Rivers come together. The Forks is home to various shops, restaurants, and events and is a popular destination for locals and tourists alike.

Other popular attractions in Winnipeg include the Manitoba Museum, which offers a glimpse into the province's natural and cultural history, and the Winnipeg Art Gallery, which features a collection of contemporary and indigenous art.

Winnipeg is also home to a thriving arts and culture scene, with numerous museums, galleries, and performance spaces. The city hosts several festivals annually, including the Winnipeg Folk Festival and the Winnipeg Fringe Theatre Festival.

name: Condo in Winnipeg · ★4.66 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Wander around downtown for the day and you'll find yourself surrounded by Winnipeg’s famed architecture, a mix of turn of the 19th century and early 20th century masonry (or, as we like to say, stone skyscrapers) and modern glass buildings. You’ll also be introduced to downtown’s culinary scene, where gourmet sandwiches, food trucks, and handcrafted cocktails are aplenty.

Above all, you’ll see the people that make this place so great - like the singer/songwriters on stage at downtown’s many live music venues, the tour guides who can introduce you to landmarks like the much-photographed oculus at the VIA Rail Station, the chefs and shop keepers of the trendy boutiques and restaurants, and our famed Golden Boy, who looks out from his perch on top of the Manitoba Legislative Building.

name: Home in Winnipeg · ★5.0 · 5 bedrooms · 6 beds · 2 baths
neighborhood_overview:
Rich in history Point Douglas is one of Winnipeg's earliest settlements. Barber house, Ross house Museum are both open for viewing in summer months.

This home offers significant history in itself. Situated in Winnipeg's first and only red-light district 1909-1912 and Purchased from the original family, this home was converted from a brothel, turned rooming house, duplex and now single family home.

*house is not haunted. Smudged by indigenous elder and blessed by a Christian minister*

Today North Point Douglas is a very diverse and rapidly changing neighborhood. Strong in activism, arts and indigenous culture the area has slowly battled a losing fight against gentrification. Surrounded on 3 sides by the red river this neighbourhood offers beautiful views and easy accessibility to all the great things Winnipeg offers.

Only a few minute drive to The Forks/Human Rights Museum to fulfill your sightseeing needs. Or if you're feeling up to it, it's

Location

The heart of Winnipeg's French community, St. Boniface is a historic neighbourhood with lots to offer. From culturally rich food, to quaint cafes to artisanal chocolate shops - a food lover will not be disappointed with what this area has to offer. After a bite to eat stroll the popular Provencher Boulevard that leads up to the elegant and beautiful Provencher Bridge. This bridge connects St.Boniface to downtown Winnipeg. 

Steps away from our rental are two of Winnipeg's biggest attractions - the Canadian Museum for Human Rights (CMHR) and The Forks. The CMHR is an architectural marvel and one of it's kind in Canada. The Forks is located at the junction of the Red and Assiniboine Rivers. It is a large community hub that offers shopping, dining, and recreational activities year round.

We are just one block from Osborne street, where you will find nightclubs, pubs, restaurants, and trendy shops. We are also one block in the other direction from the beginning of the Corydon Avenue strip, known as Little Italy, where you will find a blend of both affordable and upscale restaurants and lounges. Indeed, within 10 minutes -on foot- of our front door, you will find over 50 restaurants.

name: Rental unit in Winnipeg · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
Condo in Winnipeg · ★4.94 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Winnipeg's Exchange District is one of the most iconic and vibrant neighbourhoods in Winnipeg. This national historic site features an exceptional collection of heritage buildings built between 1880 and 1920. Nicknamed the “Chicago of the North”, the Exchange features more than 150 immaculate heritage buildings within 20-square-blocks.

These buildings and tree-lined streets, which were once warehouses and “terra cotta skyscrapers” that housed financial institutions, have since become Winnipeg’s cultural hub, blanketed with restaurants, galleries, gourmet donut and coffee shops, hip clothing, lifestyle and design stores.

It’s also become the home to many Winnipeg businesses including graphic design and architecture firms, tech start-ups via Innovation Alley, and photography studios. Above the streets many of these older buildings’ floors have been converted into stylish studio apartments where a lot of the city’s hip set have started to migrate.

name: Condo in Winnipeg · ★4.84 · 1 bedroom · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Downtown Winnipeg is an area of Winnipeg located near the confluence of the Red and Assiniboine rivers. It is the oldest urban area in Winnipeg, and is home to the city's commercial core, city hall, the seat of Manitoba's provincial government, and a number of major attractions and institutions. Neighbourhoods in the downtown area include the Exchange District, Central Park, The Forks, and Chinatown. The downtown area is roughly 3 square kilometres (740 acres). Winnipeg Square, Bell MTS Place, Portage Place, are all located on the downtown section of Portage Avenue. On Main Street are Winnipeg's City Hall, Union Station, and the Manitoba Centennial Centre, which includes the Manitoba Museum, the Planetarium, the Centennial Concert Hall, and the Winnipeg Railway Museum.

neighborhood_overview:
Winnipeg's Exchange District is one of the most iconic and vibrant neighbourhoods in Winnipeg. This national historic site features an exceptional collection of heritage buildings built between 1880 and 1920.
Nicknamed the “Chicago of the North”, the Exchange features more than 150 immaculate heritage buildings within 20-square-blocks.

These buildings and tree-lined streets, which were once warehouses and “terra cotta skyscrapers”, have since become Winnipeg’s cultural hub, blanketed with restaurants, galleries, gourmet donut and coffee shops, hip clothing, lifestyle and design stores.

It’s also become the home to many Winnipeg businesses including graphic design and architecture firms, tech start-ups and photography studios. Above the streets many of these older buildings’ floors have been converted into stylish studio lofts, like this one.

neighborhood_overview:
If you love nice patios, al fresco dining, gelato, and an all round jovial atmosphere, then Corydon Avenue is for you. Once known as Winnipeg’s “Little Italy,” Corydon Ave is a destination district, one which is popular with visitors and locals alike for people watching, shopping and dining. In the summer, you’ll find shady patios packed with people sipping sangria and beer. On Friday and Saturday nights during July and August, you’ll find a live music during the “Dancing on the Avenue” concert series featuring everything from 50s rock to jazz to blues.

A vast array of cuisines is available – from Japanese ramen, to Korean BBQ, to locally-sourced burgers, to sushi – while classic Italiano institutions serving gelati and strong shots of espresso are evident throughout. It’s also still the neighbourhood to go watch European sports, should the World Cup or Euros be on.

St. Boniface is home to one of the largest francophone communities west of the Great Lakes, and it is the heart of Manitoba's French history and culture. While here, you can stroll along le boulevard Provencher and visit boutiques and quaint cafés along the way.

Gaining buzz in the French Quarter is Marion Street Eatery, which serves stylized comfort food for breakfast and lunch. neighborhood_overview:
Wander around downtown for the day and you'll find yourself surrounded by Winnipeg’s famed architecture, a mix of turn of the 19th century and early 20th century masonry (or, as we like to say, stone skyscrapers) and modern glass buildings. You’ll also be introduced to downtown’s culinary scene, where gourmet sandwiches, food trucks, and handcrafted cocktails are aplenty.

Above all, you’ll see the people that make this place so great - like the singer/songwriters on stage at downtown’s many live music venues, the tour guides who can introduce you to landmarks like the much-photographed oculus at the VIA Rail Station, the chefs and shop keepers of the trendy boutiques and restaurants, and our famed Golden Boy, who looks out from his perch on top of the Manitoba Legislative Building.

neighborhood_overview:
Wolseley is an incredibly diverse neighbourhood where the cool kids, families, artsy types, and all round good people call home. It’s affectionately known as “The Granola Belt” of Winnipeg and it features one of the most intact pre-1930 residential areas in Canada. It’s pretty much the poster child of whimsical charm in Winnipeg.

The Wolseley is overlooked as a residential area with a bohemian reputation and pedestrian-only summer roads. This neighbourhood’s beautiful old houses, charming cafes and artistic alleyways make it a must-see!
host_about:
Welcome to our home! Welcome to your next adventure!

We are a couple from Europe living in Winnipeg for 7 years (Irene) and 25 years (Dario).
We are passionate about art, culture, architecture, design, travel and Beauty in all its expressions!
With European artistic influences, we have created this unique place to make your getaway unforgettable. In addition to our hospitality and attention to detail, we take advantage of Irene's decades of experience in tourism and our sparkling personalities, just like our product!
We look forward to meeting you and providing you with a flawless experience!

We love to travel and when we do, we want nothing less than authenticity, to experience the local life and to get the best out of every experience! It is with this same perspective that we take pride in creating great experiences for our guests!

Together we speak 7 languages: French, English, Spanish, Russian, Italian (a bit), Serbian and Croatian!

Welcome to Fort Richmond, a vibrant and welcoming neighborhood in Winnipeg! Nestled in the south end of the city, Fort Richmond offers a perfect blend of tranquility and convenience, making it an ideal destination for residents and visitors alike.

**Community Atmosphere**: Fort Richmond boasts a strong sense of community, with friendly neighbors and a warm atmosphere. You'll find a mix of families, students, and professionals, creating a diverse and inclusive environment.

**Education Hub**: Home to the University of Manitoba's Fort Garry campus, this neighborhood attracts students from all over the world. The presence of the university adds a youthful and energetic vibe to the area.

**Parks and Green Spaces**: Fort Richmond is blessed with several parks and green spaces, offering a perfect retreat for nature lovers and outdoor enthusiasts. Enjoy leisurely walks, picnics, or outdoor activities in these serene spots.

neighborhood_overview:
Overview

The home is nestled in a tranquil and friendly neighborhood of Winnipeg, Manitoba. Its prime and well-connected location offers a relaxing retreat less than five minutes from the booming downtown.

One of the top attractions in Winnipeg is The Forks, a historic meeting place where the Red and Assiniboine Rivers come together. The Forks is home to various shops, restaurants, and events and is a popular destination for locals and tourists alike.

Other popular attractions in Winnipeg include the Manitoba Museum, which offers a glimpse into the province's natural and cultural history, and the Winnipeg Art Gallery, which features a collection of contemporary and indigenous art.

Winnipeg is also home to a thriving arts and culture scene, with numerous museums, galleries, and performance spaces. The city hosts several festivals annually, including the Winnipeg Folk Festival and the Winnipeg Fringe Theatre Festival.

name: Home in Winnipeg · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview: Located in the South Osborne / Lord Roberts area of Winnipeg, this is a very desirable safe area. Rapid transit is just two blocks away and walking for groceries or to a morning coffee shop takes about 15 minutes.
host_about:
Hello and thank-you for your interest in my home. I've lived in Winnipeg for over 20 years and can help with any questions about the city - as well as the many events. 

My house in an amazing area and it's unlike many other airbnb's. It has a dog playground. The back yard is equipped with a cute dog house, hay bales and is fully enclosed with a new six foot fence. Inside I always have a kennel, bowls and an oversized dog mat setup. That said it's always clean and tidy. 

I work at a travel lodge a few hours away with my dogs. So, the place is for rent while I'm gone. It's a place I love and a sanctuary for all. 

Previously I was a Commercial Property Manager and a Real Estate Photographer. With this experience and attention to detail, providing quality accommodation comes second nature.

As a world traveler, I know the comforts that make a stay relaxing. Things like a full kitchen, morning coffee/tea, books to read, snacks upon arrival and even just knowledgable neighbours really make a difference.

In the reviews you will see many for other properties I've managed. The property is new but the host (myself) is the same. So you'll see I'm quite experienced and love to help people have fantastic vacations. 


I hope you enjoy your stay and if there is anything I can do to make it better just let us know.

host_about:
Hi there!

We are so excited to host you during your stay! Being avid travelers ourselves, we love the experience AirBNB has provided being able to experience life as one of the locals in wherever we're going. We wanted to give the same experience to people visiting our properties and be able to provide the most incredible accommodations to all of our guests.

We obsess over every detail and have an incredible team to ensure our properties are cleaned and maintained to the highest standard prior to your visit. Our guests' book with us for a reason, and we'd love to host you for you to find out why.

Currently we are helping homeowners from across the country manage their investment properties / vacation rentals by welcoming guests into their homes through our property management business, Blue Bell Properties. We are a hands-on short term rental management company and handle all the logistical work that goes into managing short term rentals. Showcasing these properties to look their best and bring in higher returns for our partners and investors is just a small part of what we do.

If you like the idea of short term rentals, but simply don't want to handle the day to day management of dealing with guests, coordinating maid staff and maintenance, managing your calendar, and marketing your property to earn the highest nightly rates possible, feel free to contact us and we'd be happy to have a complimentary consultation with you and see if we are a good fit for your needs. We look forward to serving you and making your short term rental experience as hands off as possible and something you’ll love for years to come!

We hope you enjoy your stay with us and can experience everything our amazing properties have to offer!

neighborhood_overview:
The Winnipeg suburb of Charleswood is a calm and lovely place with many of nearby services and things to explore. Here are some noteworthy features in the area:

Charleswood is a terrific destination for those who love the outdoors and the great outdoors because of its network of nature paths that loop through lovely parks and natural regions.

Local eateries and businesses: There are several little shops, cafes, and restaurants in the region that provide a variety of gastronomic delights and shopping opportunities. From quaint cafes and boutique boutiques to artisanal bakers, everything is here.

Charleswood is a short drive from Assiniboine Park, one of Winnipeg's most well-liked attractions. The park offers a zoo, walking trails, lovely gardens, and a range of leisure and cultural pursuits.

University of Manitoba: Because of its proximity to the university, Charleswood is a well-liked vacation spot for tourists and academics.

I'm Taiwo, a culinary artist, avid traveler, music lover, and successful business owner. With my passion for all things beautiful, delicious, and culturally diverse, I've made a name for myself in the world of food and hospitality, having opened my own restaurant and built a reputation for creating stunning dishes and memorable dining experiences.

As a former Senior Logistics Officer, I have a unique perspective on the importance of comfort and convenience, and I've incorporated these principles into our Airbnb listing. My home is designed to provide guests with a relaxing and worry-free stay, whether they're here for business or pleasure. From the cozy bedding to the fully equipped kitchen, I've thought of every detail to make your stay as enjoyable as possible.

When I'm not in the kitchen or at my restaurant, you can find me exploring new destinations, discovering new music, and soaking up local cultures. My love for travel and adventure has taken me to some of the most amazing places in the world, and I can't wait to share my stories and recommendations with you.

So, whether you're a foodie looking to experience the best of local cuisine, a music lover looking for new tunes, or simply in need of a comfortable and convenient place to stay, I'm here to make your stay unforgettable. I look forward to hosting you soon!

One more thing....I will spoil you with some Naija cuisines if you permit me.

I'm Taiwo, a culinary artist, avid traveler, music lover, and successful business owner. With my passion for all things beautiful, delicious, and culturally diverse, I've made a name for myself in the world of food and hospitality, having opened my own restaurant and built a reputation for creating stunning dishes and memorable dining experiences.

As a former Senior Logistics Officer, I have a unique perspective on the importance of comfort and convenience, and I've incorporated these principles into our Airbnb listing. My home is designed to provide guests with a relaxing and worry-free stay, whether they're here for business or pleasure. From the cozy bedding to the fully equipped kitchen, I've thought of every detail to make your stay as enjoyable as possible.

When I'm not in the kitchen or at my restaurant, you can find me exploring new destinations, discovering new music, and soaking up local cultures. My love for travel and adventure has taken me to some of the most amazing places in the world, and I can't wait to share my stories and recommendations with you.

So, whether you're a foodie looking to experience the best of local cuisine, a music lover looking for new tunes, or simply in need of a comfortable and convenient place to stay, I'm here to make your stay unforgettable. I look forward to hosting you soon!

One more thing....I will spoil you with some Naija cuisines if you permit me.

neighborhood_overview:
One of the highlights of the Lord Roberts neighbourhood is the iconic pedestrian bridge that spans the Red River. The bridge offers stunning views of the river and surrounding landscape, and is a popular spot for walking, cycling, and taking in the scenery.

Nearby, you'll also find the famous Bridge Drive-In (BDI), known for its delicious ice cream and sweet treats. The BDI has been a Winnipeg institution for decades, and is a must-visit spot for anyone in the area.

In addition to these attractions, Lord Roberts offers several parks and green spaces of its own, such as McKittrick Park. These parks offer plenty of space for outdoor activities such as picnicking, sports, and leisurely walks.

name: Condo in Winnipeg · ★4.82 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Tuxedo is Winnipeg’s “oh la la” area. Sprawling mansions, lush greenery and gorgeous character homes are found in this upscale suburban neighborhood. In the early 1900s Tuxedo was originally conceived as “Tuxedo Park,” an exclusive residential suburb.

Assiniboine Park is the area’s biggest attraction. This beautiful green space features a zoo, a duck pond, the Leo Mol Sculpture Garden, a new children's adventure playground area, Qualico Family Centre, trails, English gardens, restaurants, a pavilion and a stage for musical performances throughout the summer. The Park Café is warm, inviting and a picture-perfect place to have a meal with family and friends. Located inside the Qualico Family Centre, the child-friendly café is charming and affordable. If you want an up close and personal meeting with polar bears, then The Tundra Grill is sure to chill to the bone. This restaurant, located in the Assiniboine Park Zoo, offers exclusive views of playing polar bears while you dine.

name: Condo in Winnipeg · ★4.60 · 2 bedrooms · 2 beds · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
The Exchange District is a vibrant and historic neighbourhood located in the heart of downtown Winnipeg, Manitoba. This area is known for its beautiful architecture, rich cultural heritage, and lively arts scene.

The Exchange District is home to over 150 heritage buildings, many of which were built in the late 19th and early 20th centuries. These buildings are a testament to the city's past and have been beautifully restored to house a variety of businesses, including restaurants, cafes, art galleries, and boutique shops.

One of the most famous landmarks in the Exchange District is the Royal Manitoba Theatre Centre, which hosts a variety of plays and musicals throughout the year. The area is also home to the Manitoba Museum, which features exhibits on the province's history, as well as the Winnipeg Art Gallery, which houses an impressive collection of contemporary and indigenous art.

Hi there!

We are so excited to host you during your stay! Being avid travelers ourselves, we love the experience AirBNB has provided being able to experience life as one of the locals in wherever we're going. We wanted to give the same experience to people visiting our properties and be able to provide the most incredible accommodations to all of our guests.

We obsess over every detail and have an incredible team to ensure our properties are cleaned and maintained to the highest standard prior to your visit. Our guests' book with us for a reason, and we'd love to host you for you to find out why.

Currently we are helping homeowners from across the country manage their investment properties / vacation rentals by welcoming guests into their homes through our property management business, Blue Bell Properties. We are a hands-on short term rental management company and handle all the logistical work that goes into managing short term rentals. Showcasing these properties to look their best and bring in higher returns for our partners and investors is just a small part of what we do.

If you like the idea of short term rentals, but simply don't want to handle the day to day management of dealing with guests, coordinating maid staff and maintenance, managing your calendar, and marketing your property to earn the highest nightly rates possible, feel free to contact us and we'd be happy to have a complimentary consultation with you and see if we are a good fit for your needs. We look forward to serving you and making your short term rental experience as hands off as possible and something you’ll love for years to come!

We hope you enjoy your stay with us and can experience everything our amazing properties have to offer!

neighborhood_overview:
The Bridgwater area in Winnipeg, Manitoba is a thriving and rapidly developing neighborhood located in the southwest part of the city. This modern and family-friendly community offers a perfect blend of residential charm, natural beauty, and convenient amenities.

One of the highlights of the Bridgwater area is its proximity to the breathtaking South Winnipeg Parkway. Residents can enjoy scenic walks or bike rides along the riverfront trails, taking in the tranquil surroundings and lush greenery. The area also offers access to nearby parks, providing ample opportunities for outdoor activities, picnics, and leisurely strolls.

Bridgwater is well-planned and designed with a focus on creating a welcoming and inclusive community. The neighborhood features an array of meticulously crafted homes, including single-family houses, townhomes, and condominiums. The architecture is diverse, combining modern aesthetics with functional designs, offering a range of housing options

host_about:
Hi there!

We are so excited to host you during your stay! Being avid travelers ourselves, we love the experience AirBNB has provided being able to experience life as one of the locals in wherever we're going. We wanted to give the same experience to people visiting our properties and be able to provide the most incredible accommodations to all of our guests.

We obsess over every detail and have an incredible team to ensure our properties are cleaned and maintained to the highest standard prior to your visit. Our guests' book with us for a reason, and we'd love to host you for you to find out why.

Currently we are helping homeowners from across the country manage their investment properties / vacation rentals by welcoming guests into their homes through our property management business, Blue Bell Properties. We are a hands-on short term rental management company and handle all the logistical work that goes into managing short term rentals. Showcasing these properties to look their best and bring in higher returns for our partners and investors is just a small part of what we do.

If you like the idea of short term rentals, but simply don't want to handle the day to day management of dealing with guests, coordinating maid staff and maintenance, managing your calendar, and marketing your property to earn the highest nightly rates possible, feel free to contact us and we'd be happy to have a complimentary consultation with you and see if we are a good fit for your needs. We look forward to serving you and making your short term rental experience as hands off as possible and something you’ll love for years to come!

We hope you enjoy your stay with us and can experience everything our amazing properties have to offer!

It welcomes you into a lively world of art galleries, theatres, and a buzzing arts scene. When it comes to food, you have plenty of choices, from cozy cafes to fancy restaurants that cater to all tastes. The district has many fun things to do, like theatres, live music spots, and places to hang out at night. If you enjoy shopping, you'll love the many unique stores and craft shops. It's also close to cool places like the Canada Life Centre and Human Rights Museum, which makes it even better. The Exchange District has a rich history, and its festivals and events celebrating art, culture, and community create a warm and welcoming atmosphere. Staying here gives you the perfect chance to experience Winnipeg's history, culture, and art while enjoying the modern comforts of the city. It's an open invitation to have a real and unforgettable Winnipeg experience.

name: Loft in Winnipeg · ★4.75 · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath
neighborhood_overview:
Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada
You will be in a quiet yet dynamic residential neighborhood which is considered a bit of a "hidden gem".

The Scotia Heights neighborhood is east of Main Street and runs from Saint Johns Park to Kildonan Park. Scotia Street, which is 5 min away by foot, runs parallel to the red river and is closed on holidays and Sundays for pedestrian and bike traffic only. You'll also be a 5 min walk to St John's Park, a riverside green space and 4 min drive will take you over to Kildonan Park and Rainbow Stage, an outdoor theatre where you can catch a musical theatre production. Kildonan Park also offers walking trails, and a seasonal pool/waterpark.

Downtown and Exchange District are very easily reached, and only a 7 minute drive away.

neighborhood_overview:
The Forks:

This neighborhood is adjacent to The Forks, a historic meeting place at the confluence of the Red and Assiniboine Rivers, where you can find markets, dining, and entertainment.

Festival du Voyageur:

Saint Boniface hosts the Festival du Voyageur, Western Canada's largest winter festival, celebrating the region's fur-trading and Métis heritage.

Saint Boniface Cathedral:

The neighborhood is home to the iconic St. Boniface Cathedral, which is one of the city's most recognizable landmarks and has a rich history dating back to 1818.

Residents:

Several notable individuals, including author Gabrielle Roy and musician Daniel Lavoie, have called Saint Boniface their home.

Architecture:

You'll find a mix of architectural styles in Saint Boniface, from historic buildings to modern structures, creating a visually captivating environment.

Cultural Attractions:
St. Boniface is often referred to as the "French Quarter" of Winnipeg. It's home to several cultural attractions that showcase the neighborhood's rich history. The St. Boniface Museum, St. Boniface Cathedral, and Le Musée de Saint-Boniface are must-visit sites for those interested in the area's cultural heritage.

Charleswood is situated in one of Winnipeg's most excellent locations. You won't have many reasons to leave the neighbourhood because there is a ton of local dining, shopping, and recreational options. However, there are plenty of direct routes to get to your destination, thanks to the neighbourhood's four main streets: Grant Avenue, Corydon Avenue, Roblin Boulevard, and Wilkes Avenue on the south side, and the Perimeter Highway on the west.

Numerous options are available in Charleswood to meet all of your shopping needs. The brand-new Outlet Mall has everything you need, from apparel to home décor. Including the only IKEA in the city, it is located on the southwest side of the region!

There are several local eateries nearby, such as Taverna Rodos, the Roblin Grill, the Gates on Roblin, and many more! Grocery stores nearby include Safeway and No Frills. Banks in the region include RBC, BMO, and TD Canada Trust.

River Heights is a picturesque and highly sought-after neighborhood known for its lush greenery, tree-lined streets, and walkable charm. This well-established community offers a serene and inviting atmosphere, making it a great place to live and explore.

Tree-Lined Streets:
One of the defining features of River Heights is its abundance of trees that line the residential streets. Towering elms, oaks, and maples create a canopy of greenery, providing shade in the warmer months and a stunning display of colors during the fall. The neighborhood's commitment to preserving its natural beauty is evident in the care taken to maintain these beautiful trees, contributing to a visually appealing environment.
